  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_special_health_authority">Special Health Authority</xref>
 is an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_special_health_authority">Special Health Authority</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_special_health_authority">SpHA</xref>
) provides a health service to the whole of England, not just to a local community, for example, the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nhs_business_services_authority">NHS Business Services Authority</xref>
, 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_research_authority">Health Research Authority</xref>
  
    <span class="goog_qs-tidbit goog_qs-tidbit-1">etc</span>
 .  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_special_health_authority">Special Health Authorities</xref>
 are independent, but can be subject to ministerial direction in the same way as other NHS bodies.  </p>
  <p>
For further information on 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_special_health_authority">Special Health Authorities</xref>
, see the NHS website at:  </p>
